&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;METHOD 1: GET&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
Type &lt;a href="http://localhost:8000/test" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;http://localhost:8000/test&lt;/a&gt; to retrieve the data from your database.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fmy4l23ljzcnvgacka5tt.png" class="article-body-image-wrapper"&gt;&lt;img src="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fmy4l23ljzcnvgacka5tt.png" alt="retrieve data using postman" width="776" height="385"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(As you can see, when you type this down our database is still empty. We will change that by using the POST method.)&lt;/p&gt;

