## üó£Ô∏è 10 Essential Phrases (50 is a lot! Start here):

1. **Arigatou gozaimasu** (Ah-ree-gah-toe go-zai-mass) ‚Äì Thank you.
2. **Sumimasen** (Su-me-mah-sen) ‚Äì Excuse me/Sorry.
3. **Kore o kudasai** (Ko-re oh ku-dah-sai) ‚Äì I‚Äôll take this, please.
4. **Okaikei onegaishimasu** (Oh-kai-kay oh-neh-guy-she-mass) ‚Äì Check, please.
5. **...wa doko desu ka?** (...wa doh-ko dess-ka?) ‚Äì Where is ...?
6. **Eigo?** (Ay-go?) ‚Äì English?
7. **Oishii!** (Oy-shee!) ‚Äì Delicious!
8. **Wakarimasen** (Wah-kah-ree-mah-sen) ‚Äì I don't understand.
9. **Hai / Iie** (Hi / Ee-eh) ‚Äì Yes / No.
10. **Irasshaimase!** (Ee-ra-shai-ma-seh) ‚Äì Welcome! (You‚Äôll hear this in every shop).

---

## üçµ History of the Tea Ceremony (*Chanoyu*)

* **9th Century:** Tea arrives from China via monks.
* **12th Century:** Zen monk Eisai introduces powdered green tea (matcha).
* **15th Century:** It evolves from a luxury for elites into a spiritual practice.
* **16th Century:** **Sen no Rikyu** perfects the "Wabi-cha" style, emphasizing simplicity, humility, and the aesthetic of imperfection (*Wabi-sabi*).

---

## ‚õ©Ô∏è Top 10 Etiquette Rules

1. **No Tipping:** It can actually be seen as confusing or rude.
2. **Escalators:** Stand on the **Left** in Tokyo; **Right** in Osaka.
3. **Silence on Trains:** No phone calls; keep talking to a whisper.
4. **Trash:** There are no public bins. Carry a small bag for your trash.
5. **Shoes Off:** Remove shoes at temple entrances and indoor restaurants with tatami.
6. **Chopsticks:** Never stick them vertically in rice (funeral rite).
7. **Bowing:** A small nod is enough for most interactions.
8. **Tattoos:** Check "tattoo-friendly" lists if you plan to visit an Onsen (hot spring).
9. **Walking &amp;amp; Eating:** Generally frowned upon; step to the side of the street to eat.
10. **Cash Trays:** Place money in the small tray at the counter, not directly in hands.

---

## üì∂ Best Pocket Wi-Fi &amp;amp; üöΩ The Toilet Guide

* **Wi-Fi:** **Japan Wireless** or **Ninja WiFi** are the industry leaders. Pick up at the airport.
* **The Toilet:** 1.  **The Panel:** Usually on the wall or the side of the seat.
2.  **The Icons:** Blue spray = Rear; Pink spray = Front/Feminine.
3.  **Stop:** The big orange/red square button.
4.  **Flush:** Often a separate lever on the tank or a sensor on the wall labeled **Â§ß** (Big) or **Â∞è** (Small).

**Would you like me to find the specific cherry blossom forecast dates for your travel window?**
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proper Prompt:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Prompt:

I am a complete beginner with zero coding experience. I want to learn Python so I can eventually automate simple tasks at my office job.

Please give me a 4-week learning roadmap. For each week, tell me:

What concept to focus on

One specific practice exercise

Which free resource to use (website or YouTube channel)

Assume I can study 1 hour per day.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;





&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Output:

Learning to code is a superpower for the modern office, and Python is the perfect "Swiss Army Knife" for it. Since you have 1 hour a day, we‚Äôll focus on the "80/20 rule": learning the 20% of Python that will do 80% of your office work.

Here is your 4-week roadmap to becoming an office automation hero.

---

## **Week 1: The Building Blocks**

* **Focus:** **Syntax, Variables, and Data Types.** You need to learn how to store information (like names, prices, or dates) and how to talk to the computer.
* **Practice Exercise:** Create a "Salary Calculator." Ask the user for their hourly rate and hours worked per week, then have Python print out their total monthly pay after a 10% tax deduction.
* **Resource:** **[Programming with Mosh (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/user/programmingwithmosh)** ‚Äì Watch his "Python Tutorial for Beginners" (first 60 minutes).

---

## **Week 2: The "Brain" (Logic &amp;amp; Loops)**

* **Focus:** **If-statements and Loops.** This is where automation happens. "If" statements let Python make decisions (e.g., *if* the price is over $100, flag it), and "Loops" let Python do repetitive work (e.g., check *every* row in a list).
* **Practice Exercise:** Build a "Password Validator." Write a script that asks for a password. If the password is "Secret123", print "Access Granted." If not, use a loop to let them try again up to 3 times.
* **Resource:** **[FreeCodeCamp (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/c/Freecodecamp)** ‚Äì Search for their "Scientific Computing with Python" playlist or their 4-hour Python beginner course.

---

## **Week 3: Handling Files &amp;amp; Text**

* **Focus:** **Reading and Writing Files.** In an office, your data lives in files. You‚Äôll learn how to open a `.txt` or `.csv` file, change the text inside, and save a new version.
* **Practice Exercise:** The "Automatic File Organizer." Create a script that looks at a list of filenames (like `report_2025.txt`, `image1.jpg`, `data.csv`) and "sorts" them by printing out which folder they should go into based on their extension.
* **Resource:** **[Automate the Boring Stuff with Python](https://automatetheboringstuff.com/)** ‚Äì Read **Chapter 9: Reading and Writing Files** (the website is free to read).

---

## **Week 4: The Office Superpower (Excel &amp;amp; CSV)**

* **Focus:** **The Pandas Library.** Most office work is just moving data around in Excel. Python has a tool called "Pandas" that can read 10,000 rows of Excel data in a fraction of a second.
* **Practice Exercise:** Download a sample CSV of sales data. Use Python to find the total sum of the "Sales" column and save only the rows where the "Status" is "Pending" into a new file.
* **Resource:** **[Corey Schafer (YouTube)](https://www.youtube.com/user/schafer5)** ‚Äì Look for his "Pandas Tutorial" series. He is widely considered the best teacher for clear, technical breakdowns.

---

### **How to stay on track:**

1. **Don't memorize:** You don't need to remember every command. Professional coders Google things 50 times a day.
2. **Use an IDE:** Download **VS Code** (free) to write your code. It will highlight your errors and make learning much easier.
3. **Consistency &amp;gt; Intensity:** 1 hour every day is much better than a 7-hour marathon on Sunday.

**Would you like me to generate a simple "starter script" for Week 1 that you can try running right now?**
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;h2&gt;


4. Not Iterating
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prompt engineering is &lt;strong&gt;iterative&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
Refine ‚Üí Test ‚Üí Improve.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


5. Not Including Constraints
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tell AI both:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What to do&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;What &lt;strong&gt;not&lt;/strong&gt; to do&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


6. Forgetting to Specify Output Format
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LLMs default to unstructured paragraphs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bullet points&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;JSON&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Step-by-step&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Code blocks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structured outputs improve clarity and usability&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


7. Not Using Prompting Techniques
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Without techniques, you‚Äôre &lt;strong&gt;underutilizing AI&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Step-by-Step Guide to Effective Prompt Engineering
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fg3beepec9z9jwzi9dzzh.png" class="article-body-image-wrapper"&gt;&lt;img src="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fg3beepec9z9jwzi9dzzh.png" alt="(Source: CertiProf)" width="800" height="450"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Photo Source: CertiProf)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not all prompting techniques are equal. Each produces different behavioral responses.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using the wrong technique may cause:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hallucinations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Token waste&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logical failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before prompting, choose an LLM such as Google Gemini, ChatGPT, or another preferred model. Prompting techniques generally work across platforms.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Core Prompting Techniques
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


1. Role Prompting
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assign a role to shape tone, expertise, and reasoning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Template
&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Role: [Assign a role]

Task: [Define the task]

Context: [Provide necessary data]

Constraint: [Define limitations]
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;h3&gt;


Example (Software Development)
&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Role: Act as a Senior Frontend Developer who mentors junior developers.

Task: Review my CSS code below. I am trying to center a "Profile Card"
perfectly in the middle of the web page.

Context:
.background-container {
display: flex;
justify-content: center;
}

Constraint: You are strictly forbidden from giving me the missing CSS
properties. Instead, explain the difference between the "main axis" and the
"cross axis" in Flexbox. Then ask me one guiding question.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;Role prompting shapes how the AI behaves ‚Äî mentor, critic, tutor, consultant, etc.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


2. Zero-Shot Prompting
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No examples are provided. The AI relies purely on its training.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Template
&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Instruction: Define the rule
Context: Provide necessary data
Task: Generate response
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;h3&gt;


Best for:
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Summarization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sentiment classification&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Simple transformations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


3. Few-Shot Prompting
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Provide examples to establish a pattern.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Template
&lt;/h3&gt;



&lt;div class="highlight js-code-highlight"&gt;
&lt;pre class="highlight plaintext"&gt;&lt;code&gt;Context 1: Example input
Output 1: Example output

Context 2: Example input
Output 2: Example output

Context n: New input
Output n:
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;This improves consistency and formatting accuracy.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


4. Chain-of-Thought Prompting
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Encourages step-by-step reasoning.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideal for:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mathematics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complex problem-solving&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Example
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Find the integral:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;‚à´ x cos(x) dx&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reasoning:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify as product of algebraic and trigonometric functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Choose Integration by Parts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Let u = x and dv = cos(x)dx.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply formula uv ‚àí ‚à´vdu.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Final Answer:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;x sin(x) + cos(x) + C&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chain-of-thought prompting improves transparency and logical clarity.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Real-World Applications of Prompt Engineering
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


Software Development
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F6uzms7xj0dwo91f6qr55.png" class="article-body-image-wrapper"&gt;&lt;img src="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2F6uzms7xj0dwo91f6qr55.png" alt="(Source: n8n Blog)" width="800" height="450"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Photo Source: n8n Blog)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AI assists with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Code generation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debugging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explaining logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Refactoring&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the quality of code depends heavily on prompt structure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role prompting&lt;/strong&gt; works well for:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Code reviews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship simulation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enforcing best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Education and Learning
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fz59a541b5v57245bkwk4.jpg" class="article-body-image-wrapper"&gt;&lt;img src="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fz59a541b5v57245bkwk4.jpg" alt="(Source: Discovery Education)" width="800" height="533"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Photo Source: Discovery Education)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AI can:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a tutor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate quizzes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide step-by-step math solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explain topics at varying levels of difficulty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chain-of-thought prompting&lt;/strong&gt; is particularly powerful in education.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But remember:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Output quality depends on input quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Ethical Considerations and Responsible Use
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fowfu6612w3ifddmgfoe6.jpg" class="article-body-image-wrapper"&gt;&lt;img src="https://media2.dev.to/dynamic/image/width=800%2Cheight=%2Cfit=scale-down%2Cgravity=auto%2Cformat=auto/https%3A%2F%2Fdev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fuploads%2Farticles%2Fowfu6612w3ifddmgfoe6.jpg" alt="(Source: TechHQ)" width="800" height="542"&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (Photo Source: TechHQ)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AI is powerful, but imperfect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Risks include:
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bias&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hallucinations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data privacy concerns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Academic dishonesty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overdependence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Avoid sharing:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal identifiers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confidential data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sensitive credentials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Responsible AI use requires awareness of institutional and company policies, as well as international ethical frameworks such as UNESCO‚Äôs principles on AI ethics.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These include:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do no harm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Privacy protection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transparency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accountability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Human oversight&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fairness and non-discrimination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;After reading this article, remember not only the techniques, but also the ethics of using AI. In our community, we stand by responsible and ethical prompt engineering.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


The Future of Human‚ÄìAI Interaction with Prompt Engineering
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AI is evolving from a niche tool into a foundational skill.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Prompt engineering is expanding into &lt;strong&gt;context engineering&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äî designing not just prompts, but entire AI interaction environments.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modern LLMs now:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ask clarifying questions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Suggest refinements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Offer structured response options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;AI is evolving alongside us.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even if AI advances rapidly, &lt;strong&gt;responsible prompt engineering ensures&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ethical outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Human-centered systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rights-based AI development&lt;/li&gt;
