&lt;h2&gt;


Checklist Usage
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Step 1: Select Project Type
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Choose from web app, mobile, AI/ML, migration.&lt;br&gt;
For composite projects, you can combine multiple types.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Step 2: Adjust Scale
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adjust checklist to project scale (small/medium/large).&lt;br&gt;
Must also consider duration and team size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Step 3: Customize
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Customize to client requirements (GDPR, ISO27001, etc.), tech stack, special requirements (real-time processing, multi-language, etc.).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;


Step 4: AI-Augmented Review (Optional)
&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use AI task breakdown tools to generate additional tasks from your project specs. Compare AI-generated results with your checklist to catch items you might have missed. AI can suggest tasks based on your tech stack, project type, and common patterns.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


Digital Checklist Template
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Managing checklist digitally is more efficient.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Template Structure&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Info: Name, type, scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tasks by Phase: Planning, design, development, testing, deployment, operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Each Task: Name, status, assignee, time required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Managing with this structure allows project progress without omissions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;


Key Summary
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There's no perfect checklist.&lt;br&gt;
But there is &lt;strong&gt;a checklist that keeps evolving&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Checklist Evolution Process&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start with this checklist&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add tasks discovered during project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record missed tasks in retrospective&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reflect in next project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This creates your own perfect checklist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use this checklist from your next project.&lt;br&gt;
Small effort makes a big difference.&lt;/p&gt;




