&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;This schema tells Mongoose that every task document in your database will have exactly three pieces of information: a title that is a required string, a completed flag that defaults to false when a new task is created, and timestamps ‚Äî createdAt and updatedAt ‚Äî which Mongoose adds automatically when you set timestamps: true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;module.exports at the bottom makes this model available to other files in your project, specifically your routes file, which needs it to perform database operations.&lt;/p&gt;

